          <declname>ocp_or_tsd</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>get output diagnostics </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Fetch the current diagnostics from all instances, as multiple instances might be daisy chained together. Each bit in old and ocp_or_tsd corresponds to one output. A set bit means that the function is active, therefore either there is an open load, an over current or a too high temperature.</para>
<para>OLD - open load OCP - over current protection TSD - thermal shutdown</para>
